&lt;li&gt;Support the annual financial audit, ensuring readiness through strong documentation and timely responses to audit requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure and report on efficiency gains from AI-enabled workflows, including hours saved in tasks such as flux analysis, reconciliations, and journal entry preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of progressive accounting experience, ideally with a mix of public accounting and industry experience in a high-growth or technology-enabled company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in managing the month-end close and financial reporting processes, with exposure to audits, internal controls, and cross-functional collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of US GAAP, financial reporting, and month-end close processes, including journal entries, reconciliations, and flux analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in process automation, systems implementations, or leveraging AI/data tools to improve accounting workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting external audits and internal control environments, including SOX readiness and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead and develop team members while managing multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems and process improvement mindset, with a track record of implementing automation or improving accounting workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
